mediaNotes: Not sure what species the buntings in the background is. The 3 consecutive chips are the yellow-throated.

this recording has multiple species in the area, including a tit flock, including Large-billed Crow (most in beginning of recording), Coal Tit (scolds in beginning of recording), Brown-eared Bulbul (mostly scolds, but some screams), Yellow-throated Bunting (both high tick notes and presumably the whisper songs). Marsh Tit was also in the flock (and also Japanese Tit, I think) and a Pygmy Woodpecker gives a loud call near the end (2:40) which I refer to as an unknown call (quickly confirmed as Pygmy Woodpecker immediately afterwards). Same recording uploaded to Large-blled Crow, Coal Tit, Brown-eared Bulbul, and Yellow-throated Bunting (and a later portion of the original recording also uploaded under Pygmy Woodpecker)
